1
00:00:29,880 --> 00:00:31,839
You can't go very far
with grades like that.

2
00:00:31,840 --> 00:00:33,959
Just like you, Dad.
You didn't do well either.

3
00:00:33,960 --> 00:00:34,880
Snow.
You know, Dad?

4
00:00:36,240 --> 00:00:39,120
I never wanted to stay here
because of you.

5
00:00:53,010 --> 00:00:55,120
Hmph, Sorn.

6
00:00:56,103 --> 00:00:59,023
Grades this bad.
Think you'll pass the entrance exam?

7
00:01:00,760 --> 00:01:03,640
Have you even thought
about where you're headed?

8
00:01:06,760 --> 00:01:08,320
You should look at your brother.

9
00:01:09,320 --> 00:01:10,960
Aren't you even a little ashamed?

10
00:01:13,390 --> 00:01:14,390
Take it.

11
00:01:29,010 --> 00:01:31,360
Keep up the good work. Good for you.

12
00:01:32,960 --> 00:01:35,040
Maybe your brother
can look up to you.

13
00:01:40,790 --> 00:01:41,840
Come help me fix the car.

14
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:43,640
Yes, sir.

15
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:01,080
Lift. Push. There.

16
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:03,840
Hold on. Just a sec.

17
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:08,160
- Here, grab it.
- Mm-hmm.

18
00:02:09,480 --> 00:02:10,480
Got it.

19
00:03:11,750 --> 00:03:12,860
What are you doing?

20
00:03:14,920 --> 00:03:16,120
Take those off right now.

21
00:03:18,210 --> 00:03:19,360
Don't ever do that again.

22
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:21,600
Understood?

23
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:26,440
I said, understood?

24
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:28,239
Yes, sir.

25
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:29,640
- Louder.
- Yes, sir.

26
00:03:30,540 --> 00:03:31,720
You too, Sorn.

27
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:33,760
Keep an eye on your brother.

28
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,740
When you can,
take him outside to play.

29
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:37,200
And teach him

30
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:41,610
what it means to be a boy.

31
00:03:44,650 --> 00:03:47,200
You can't even get through to him.
Now you want me to?

32
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:48,520
Sorn.

33
00:03:51,430 --> 00:03:52,430
Sorry, sir.

34
00:03:55,270 --> 00:03:57,480
You don't raise your voice
at me like that.

35
00:03:57,860 --> 00:03:59,000
You know how hurt he's been

36
00:03:59,720 --> 00:04:03,080
that you didn't grow up
the way he expected?

37
00:04:10,850 --> 00:04:12,240
Do you actually think that?

38
00:04:22,230 --> 00:04:23,230
I get it now.

39
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:26,920
Sun.

40
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:28,040
Uncle Sun.

41
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:49,850
Dad, why did you say that?

42
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:53,210
You know how much
that would hurt Uncle Sun?

43
00:04:56,640 --> 00:04:59,240
Save, he didn't mean it.

44
00:04:59,340 --> 00:05:01,380
He just let it slip.

45
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:03,720
He gets like this when he's angry.

46
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:07,080
You need to apologize to him.

47
00:05:10,390 --> 00:05:12,040
Dad, did you hear me?

48
00:05:12,230 --> 00:05:13,510
Of course. I'm not deaf.

49
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:15,200
Then go to him now.

50
00:05:16,030 --> 00:05:17,270
So he won't spiral over this.

51
00:05:17,950 --> 00:05:19,640
No. I don't want to look at him.

52
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:25,000
Is... liking men really that bad?

53
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:28,160
You're upset
because he's gay, right?

54
00:05:31,670 --> 00:05:33,000
Are you upset with me too?

55
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,280
Why would I be?

56
00:05:36,530 --> 00:05:37,530
Hmph.

57
00:05:40,060 --> 00:05:42,840
If I said I liked a guy,
would that make me gay?

58
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:46,680
Save, don't just say things.

59
00:05:46,960 --> 00:05:47,960
I mean it.

60
00:05:48,320 --> 00:05:50,360
Don't you dare joke about this.

61
00:05:50,770 --> 00:05:52,000
I'm not joking.

62
00:05:54,340 --> 00:05:55,640
Call it gay or whatever.

63
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:58,800
Point is that I'm admitting...

64
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,400
I like Guy.

65
00:06:03,410 --> 00:06:06,489
Save, don't say that to spite him.

66
00:06:06,490 --> 00:06:07,610
I'm serious.

67
00:06:07,850 --> 00:06:12,560
No, you're just messing with me.
You're pulling my leg.

68
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:14,960
My face looks like I'm joking?

69
00:06:15,110 --> 00:06:16,110
Save.

70
00:06:18,330 --> 00:06:19,600
This is too much.

71
00:06:20,650 --> 00:06:23,560
Mart, say something to your son.

72
00:06:24,020 --> 00:06:29,160
Well, I don't have a problem
with him liking a man.

73
00:06:29,870 --> 00:06:32,440
Dad, say something.

74
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,830
Now your nephew is also turning gay.

75
00:06:34,860 --> 00:06:36,230
Stop it, Sorn.

76
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:41,680
Stop? You taught me
what a man should be.

77
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:44,840
Or has your BL fiction
got your brain sideways?

78
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:47,640
Maybe so.

79
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,960
People change.

80
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:54,320
And I don't hold on to that anymore.

81
00:06:55,550 --> 00:06:56,960
Seriously, Dad?

82
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:58,240
Sorn.

83
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:03,160
Actually, Sun was a good kid.

84
00:07:04,280 --> 00:07:06,960
Never caused me any trouble.

85
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:09,440
I'm the one who was wrong.

86
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:11,920
Wrong...

87
00:07:12,850 --> 00:07:14,260
for pushing back against him.

88
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:20,840
And all this time...

89
00:07:24,550 --> 00:07:26,800
I've been more worried about you.

90
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:00,480
Grandpa.

91
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:02,360
Careful.

92
00:08:04,420 --> 00:08:05,640
Sit down.

93
00:08:27,270 --> 00:08:28,360
Are you alright?

94
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:39,600
When Sun was little,

95
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:44,480
he used to sit in that chair
and do his homework.

96
00:09:06,920 --> 00:09:08,480
I never had to tell him twice.

97
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:11,120
He just knew.

98
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:16,560
He'd sit there for an hour.

99
00:09:17,700 --> 00:09:19,240
Sometimes two.

100
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:22,400
Fan off the whole time.

101
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:26,040
And I never once asked
if he was hot.

102
00:09:27,040 --> 00:09:29,120
If you didn't hate him,

103
00:09:29,630 --> 00:09:30,920
why didn't you just tell him?

104
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:33,320
It's been a long time.

105
00:09:34,320 --> 00:09:35,320
Since what?

106
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:37,440
Since things got this way.

107
00:09:42,460 --> 00:09:44,520
And you're just gonna
leave it like this?

108
00:10:11,510 --> 00:10:16,160
"Sun's Grade 5 Report."

109
00:11:11,930 --> 00:11:13,320
Why did you say that, Dad?

110
00:11:13,760 --> 00:11:16,560
You know how much
that would hurt Uncle Sun?

111
00:11:34,670 --> 00:11:36,119
Sun, that's enough.

112
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:38,640
You cannot
speak to your father like that.

113
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:41,099
You know how hurt he's been

114
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:43,240
that you didn't grow up
the way he expected?

115
00:12:35,920 --> 00:12:38,370
"One week later."

116
00:12:38,860 --> 00:12:40,300
Dad, come on.

117
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:42,000
You seriously upset him.

118
00:12:42,210 --> 00:12:44,280
Don't you feel bad
and wanna make it right?

119
00:12:45,180 --> 00:12:47,920
No. His problem, not mine.

120
00:12:48,280 --> 00:12:50,320
You mean you're cutting him off
completely?

121
00:12:50,760 --> 00:12:51,760
Up to him.

122
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:57,360
We can't just cut Sun out.

123
00:12:57,960 --> 00:12:59,640
Don't be so dramatic.

124
00:13:00,410 --> 00:13:03,000
You're not that close to him.

125
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:05,280
We owe him money.

126
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:08,640
Owe him?
I never borrowed anything from him.

127
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:10,600
I did.

128
00:13:11,560 --> 00:13:15,840
When the account ran dry,
all the household expenses

129
00:13:16,350 --> 00:13:17,560
that was Sun's money.

130
00:13:18,160 --> 00:13:21,480
And you know
how we've kept things running?

131
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:23,480
Sun had a hand in all of it.

132
00:13:24,360 --> 00:13:27,480
Without him,
we wouldn't have made it to today.

133
00:13:28,450 --> 00:13:29,680
I'm sorry.

134
00:13:30,430 --> 00:13:34,170
I still owe you from last time.

135
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:36,560
Don't worry about it, Phi Mart.

136
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:39,400
Pay me when you can.

137
00:13:40,130 --> 00:13:41,960
Things are pretty tight,
aren't they?

138
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:47,320
Yeah, pretty bad. I don't know
how we're gonna get by.

139
00:13:47,790 --> 00:13:50,180
Hmm... just take it
one step at a time.

140
00:13:50,870 --> 00:13:52,080
I'll transfer it right now.

141
00:13:52,810 --> 00:13:55,610
Thank you.
Really, thank you so much.

142
00:13:56,160 --> 00:13:57,880
I feel terrible
to bother you like this.

143
00:13:58,590 --> 00:14:01,880
I won't forget this.
I really mean it.

144
00:14:04,900 --> 00:14:06,920
And I kept it from everyone...

145
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:10,880
because you'd never let me
take Sun's money.

146
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:15,160
He loves everyone.

147
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:19,600
He'd always ask me how Phi Sorn
was doing or how work was going.

148
00:14:20,670 --> 00:14:22,640
Father's health.

149
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:26,240
Save and Snow's tutoring money.

150
00:14:26,720 --> 00:14:29,360
Sun has always
treated us like family.

151
00:14:30,120 --> 00:14:33,280
What about us?
How have we repaid him?

152
00:14:34,060 --> 00:14:35,440
Not well would be bad enough.

153
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:38,520
But we went so far
as to hurt his feelings.

154
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:19,200
What, Dad?
What do you do for a living?

155
00:15:19,870 --> 00:15:21,800
You didn't do well in school either.

156
00:15:21,830 --> 00:15:22,830
Snow.

157
00:15:31,250 --> 00:15:32,560
"Dear Dad,."

158
00:15:33,620 --> 00:15:37,200
"I'm sorry for
saying mean things to you."

159
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:40,800
"I won't do it again."

160
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:42,760
"I love you, Dad."

161
00:15:47,610 --> 00:15:51,480
Snow, not now.
The grown-ups are talking.

162
00:15:53,660 --> 00:15:54,800
Go study upstairs.

163
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:43,280
What now?

164
00:16:43,560 --> 00:16:44,920
I want to go to see you.

165
00:16:45,960 --> 00:16:47,760
There's nothing left to talk about.

166
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:49,880
Everything's been settled.

167
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:53,320
Settled? Nothing's been settled.

168
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:57,360
Just a quiet dinner.
Keep you company.

169
00:16:57,810 --> 00:17:01,080
I promise to sit there
and not say a word.

170
00:17:01,660 --> 00:17:03,800
I really feel bad about
what Dad and Grandpa did.

171
00:17:05,550 --> 00:17:08,160
Fine. What time are you coming?

172
00:17:43,150 --> 00:17:45,640
Just dropping them off.
Talk it out, okay?

173
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:52,280
How much did this place run you?

174
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:54,480
Four million baht.

175
00:17:54,910 --> 00:17:56,500
How many years
left on the mortgage?

176
00:17:56,800 --> 00:18:00,020
About ten more.
I'll pay it down when I can.

177
00:18:05,650 --> 00:18:06,960
So what did you come here for?

178
00:18:07,160 --> 00:18:09,920
Don't tell me
you just wanted a tour.

179
00:18:10,810 --> 00:18:12,560
You've never shown any interest.

180
00:18:16,190 --> 00:18:17,680
Got something to say? Say it.

181
00:18:21,430 --> 00:18:23,000
Um, I...

182
00:18:23,970 --> 00:18:24,970
I...

183
00:18:25,480 --> 00:18:26,280
I...

184
00:18:26,281 --> 00:18:27,400
Just say it already.

185
00:18:31,120 --> 00:18:32,240
I'm sorry.

186
00:18:33,570 --> 00:18:34,880
For coming at you so hard.

187
00:18:37,900 --> 00:18:40,200
Deep down, I never
actually meant any of it.

188
00:18:40,840 --> 00:18:44,640
I completely lost it
because I'd just got mad with Snow.

189
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:48,400
That's it?

190
00:18:48,420 --> 00:18:49,420
No.

191
00:18:50,220 --> 00:18:53,670
And... I'm sorry.
For everything, all this time.

192
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:59,000
So I'm just a useless brother, huh?

193
00:19:00,320 --> 00:19:01,320
Who said that?

194
00:19:01,830 --> 00:19:04,450
Your face. I can tell
you're roasting me in your head.

195
00:19:05,590 --> 00:19:06,800
Yeah, I am.

196
00:19:07,530 --> 00:19:10,060
But not because you're useless.

197
00:19:10,820 --> 00:19:13,860
I'm mad because
you were never there for me.

198
00:19:14,830 --> 00:19:19,240
Every time Dad scolded me,
you never once stood up for me.

199
00:19:20,440 --> 00:19:22,880
Well, neither did you
when it was my turn.

200
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:25,120
Ahem.

201
00:19:27,760 --> 00:19:30,400
What now? Are we even?

202
00:19:31,080 --> 00:19:32,200
That's not what I mean.

203
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:36,240
I just... found out from Mart

204
00:19:36,260 --> 00:19:39,160
that you've been quietly
keeping our family afloat.

205
00:19:41,420 --> 00:19:43,000
I had you all wrong, Sun.

206
00:19:45,360 --> 00:19:46,360
Thank you.

207
00:19:48,250 --> 00:19:50,720
What was that? Couldn't hear you.

208
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:56,360
I said thank you.

209
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:00,480
Mm-hmm.

210
00:20:03,570 --> 00:20:04,570
Are we good?

211
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:05,600
Mm-hmm.

212
00:20:23,690 --> 00:20:24,690
Take it out.

213
00:20:44,020 --> 00:20:45,280
You still kept it?

214
00:20:46,360 --> 00:20:48,440
Been meaning to return it
for a long time.

215
00:20:56,810 --> 00:20:58,280
These are out of style now.

216
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:01,400
Yeah.

217
00:21:02,760 --> 00:21:04,680
Shame on me
for keeping it until now.

218
00:21:05,580 --> 00:21:07,320
Long overdue.

219
00:21:08,340 --> 00:21:09,480
I'm sorry...

220
00:21:13,320 --> 00:21:14,440
for being unkind.

221
00:21:16,480 --> 00:21:17,920
You've had it hard,

222
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:22,200
have you not?

223
00:21:32,020 --> 00:21:33,020
You've done well.

224
00:21:36,040 --> 00:21:37,520
As you always have.

225
00:21:42,960 --> 00:21:44,840
And from now on,
when you have time,

226
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:51,000
come home... and eat with us.

227
00:21:54,520 --> 00:21:55,520
Dad.

228
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:38,600
Dad, are you okay?

229
00:22:51,210 --> 00:22:55,130
Your surgery, Dad.
Gonna wait till next year?

230
00:22:57,560 --> 00:23:00,760
The doctor said there's still time
before it gets urgent.

231
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:03,300
It'll cost less,
and that'll help with the debt.

232
00:23:05,010 --> 00:23:06,710
As for the house...

233
00:23:07,360 --> 00:23:09,090
I'm not selling it no matter what.

234
00:23:10,160 --> 00:23:11,520
Don't waste our breath arguing.

235
00:23:12,080 --> 00:23:13,760
I didn't mean to force you into it.

236
00:23:15,540 --> 00:23:17,500
I see you can understand who I am.

237
00:23:18,740 --> 00:23:21,240
I think I can
understand your adamance.

238
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:24,520
Thank you.

239
00:23:26,490 --> 00:23:27,760
Phi Mart told me...

240
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:31,110
there's still a loan at the bank.

241
00:23:31,620 --> 00:23:32,679
I'd like to help.

242
00:23:32,680 --> 00:23:34,480
No. Absolutely not.

243
00:23:35,560 --> 00:23:36,560
Come on, Dad.

244
00:23:36,960 --> 00:23:38,760
I don't want your help.

245
00:23:39,360 --> 00:23:42,030
It feels like I'd owe you
more than money.

246
00:23:43,250 --> 00:23:44,930
It's nothing more than money, Dad.

247
00:23:45,920 --> 00:23:47,720
I just... want to do it.

248
00:23:48,880 --> 00:23:53,520
This money will pay off the debt.
Give me back when you can.

249
00:23:53,770 --> 00:23:56,320
Okay? It's not a handout.

250
00:24:00,370 --> 00:24:03,360
Dad, he wants to help.

251
00:24:04,270 --> 00:24:05,840
Don't turn him down again.

252
00:24:10,080 --> 00:24:11,160
And you...

253
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:13,880
won't be in trouble at all?

254
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:17,580
I'm on my own, no kids.

255
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:20,800
I can help. No problem.

256
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:26,080
Then I'll accept it.

257
00:24:36,960 --> 00:24:40,650
Save, let's talk when we get home.

258
00:24:46,480 --> 00:24:50,880
About you liking a guy.
What's that all about?

259
00:24:52,320 --> 00:24:53,560
It's like I said.

260
00:24:56,290 --> 00:24:58,600
Are you sure it is what you want?

261
00:24:59,400 --> 00:25:02,080
I don't know if it'll work out.

262
00:25:03,620 --> 00:25:05,120
But it's not wrong to try.

263
00:25:06,270 --> 00:25:09,400
I don't want to regret it.
You get that, right?

264
00:25:12,450 --> 00:25:13,450
Hmph.

265
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:18,000
When it comes to experimenting...

266
00:25:18,880 --> 00:25:21,480
at your age,
I was way worse than you.

267
00:25:23,250 --> 00:25:24,250
Figured.

268
00:25:25,830 --> 00:25:27,440
Now your grandpa came around.

269
00:25:28,080 --> 00:25:29,280
If I can't...

270
00:25:29,870 --> 00:25:32,370
I'd be a super old turtle, huh?

271
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:34,640
Just a little old.

272
00:25:36,350 --> 00:25:38,800
For being a little old,
I'm putting my foot down then.

273
00:25:39,630 --> 00:25:44,410
- Dad, seriously.
- Hmph.

274
00:25:46,250 --> 00:25:48,120
Well, I guess
I won't get grandkids?

275
00:25:48,480 --> 00:25:50,680
Oh-ho. You really think
that far ahead?

276
00:25:51,770 --> 00:25:55,560
If I marry a girl, I might
even choose not to have kids.

277
00:25:56,090 --> 00:25:57,090
Freedom and all that.

278
00:25:57,210 --> 00:25:58,960
Huh... kids these days.

279
00:25:59,740 --> 00:26:02,759
Guess what?
Two men can have kids now.

280
00:26:02,760 --> 00:26:03,600
You know?

281
00:26:03,601 --> 00:26:05,039
I just read about it.

282
00:26:05,040 --> 00:26:09,280
Scientists can
take DNA from skin cells

283
00:26:09,480 --> 00:26:11,760
and fertilize it with sperm.

284
00:26:11,790 --> 00:26:14,920
- Wow.
- Yeah, so don't worry about kids.

285
00:26:15,430 --> 00:26:17,600
- That advanced?
- Mm-hmm.

286
00:26:18,390 --> 00:26:19,300
Huh.

287
00:26:19,330 --> 00:26:23,650
Alright, alright.
Whatever you do, think it through.

288
00:26:24,080 --> 00:26:25,400
Don't mess things up.

289
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:27,680
So, you're okay with it?

290
00:26:27,710 --> 00:26:31,550
Hmph. I, alone in saying no,

291
00:26:31,570 --> 00:26:33,870
will be the lone villain
of the house.

292
00:26:35,450 --> 00:26:36,450
Come on.

293
00:26:36,920 --> 00:26:39,959
- Let me lie down.
- Heh.

294
00:26:39,960 --> 00:26:41,950
- I'm tired.
- Yeah, yeah.

295
00:26:42,950 --> 00:26:44,800
Look at you, all grown up.

296
00:27:06,360 --> 00:27:07,360
Ow.

297
00:27:07,930 --> 00:27:08,840
Save.

298
00:27:08,860 --> 00:27:10,300
Hey, you were in my way, Pheem.

299
00:27:10,450 --> 00:27:11,540
Got a job you asked for.

300
00:27:11,780 --> 00:27:12,780
- A job?
- Yeah.

301
00:27:13,110 --> 00:27:14,720
Sure, what kind?

302
00:27:15,080 --> 00:27:17,760
My mom's friend has a kid who
needs a junior high math tutor.

303
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:19,320
Pay is kinda low, though.

304
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:20,880
How low?

305
00:27:21,600 --> 00:27:23,310
My family's ten million in debt.

306
00:27:24,560 --> 00:27:25,800
- 3...
- Three hundred.

307
00:27:26,600 --> 00:27:30,200
Three hundred?
When will I pay my debt off?

308
00:27:30,520 --> 00:27:34,240
Come on. I'll send
more students your way if any.

309
00:27:34,970 --> 00:27:37,800
Fine, I'm in. Thanks a lot.
Send them over anytime.

310
00:27:38,240 --> 00:27:42,080
Hey, you want big money?
Try the entertainment industry.

311
00:27:42,470 --> 00:27:43,640
Word is it pays well.

312
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:45,000
Doing what?

313
00:27:45,480 --> 00:27:49,140
Act in a series.
You've got the look for it.

314
00:27:49,380 --> 00:27:51,400
- Me?
- Yeah.

315
00:27:51,430 --> 00:27:53,490
Nah. Any other options?

316
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:55,200
Can you afford to be picky?

317
00:27:56,520 --> 00:27:57,920
Take what you can get.

318
00:27:58,740 --> 00:28:00,650
What about your novel?
Quit?

319
00:28:01,550 --> 00:28:02,550
Hmm.

320
00:28:03,200 --> 00:28:05,890
My grandpa has cataracts.
His eyesight's getting bad.

321
00:28:06,370 --> 00:28:09,920
He's been feeling down.
Can't write at all.

322
00:28:11,890 --> 00:28:13,520
Man, one hurdle after another.

323
00:28:14,160 --> 00:28:17,000
Good thing I've got you around.

324
00:28:19,480 --> 00:28:20,160
Huh.

325
00:28:20,340 --> 00:28:22,760
You think...
I should give it a shot?

326
00:28:23,450 --> 00:28:24,450
Give what a shot?

327
00:28:24,730 --> 00:28:27,040
The showbiz thing.

328
00:28:29,380 --> 00:28:30,380
I want the money.

329
00:28:31,480 --> 00:28:32,480
Go for it then.

330
00:28:34,300 --> 00:28:36,250
The other day, I got a DM
about an audition.

331
00:28:36,720 --> 00:28:38,520
I thought it was a scam.

332
00:28:39,020 --> 00:28:40,140
Let me see.

333
00:28:41,070 --> 00:28:42,070
Here.

334
00:28:49,370 --> 00:28:50,370
What scam?

335
00:28:50,510 --> 00:28:52,880
Climax Studio. They're big.

336
00:28:54,280 --> 00:28:55,280
No way.

337
00:28:56,540 --> 00:28:57,800
DM them back right now.

338
00:28:59,200 --> 00:29:01,300
- Now?
- Yeah.

339
00:29:11,740 --> 00:29:12,740
Hello,

340
00:29:13,320 --> 00:29:14,760
sorry for the late reply.

341
00:29:14,840 --> 00:29:16,240
How may I help you?

342
00:29:16,350 --> 00:29:17,350
The audition.

343
00:29:17,370 --> 00:29:19,150
Oh, am I speaking to Save?

344
00:29:19,170 --> 00:29:22,070
Sure. Could you email me
a straight-on headshot?

345
00:29:22,100 --> 00:29:24,240
Got it. I'll send it right over.

346
00:29:26,380 --> 00:29:27,680
Thanks for the opportunity.

347
00:29:33,700 --> 00:29:34,700
What'd they say?

348
00:29:34,730 --> 00:29:36,280
They want a headshot,

349
00:29:37,160 --> 00:29:38,480
but I don't have any decent one.

350
00:29:39,930 --> 00:29:40,930
Come here.

351
00:29:42,240 --> 00:29:44,310
- Now?
- Yeah, now. Come on.

352
00:29:45,800 --> 00:29:47,520
Too stiff. Relax.

353
00:29:49,240 --> 00:29:50,240
Smile, smile.

354
00:29:51,280 --> 00:29:52,360
That's it.

355
00:29:55,320 --> 00:29:57,360
Alright, send it to them now.

356
00:29:57,760 --> 00:29:58,760
Okay.

357
00:30:01,240 --> 00:30:03,040
- This one?
- Yeah.

358
00:30:03,840 --> 00:30:04,840
Hmph.

359
00:30:07,690 --> 00:30:08,690
Here.

360
00:30:10,120 --> 00:30:11,240
Have they replied yet?

361
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:13,200
Not yet.

362
00:30:14,980 --> 00:30:15,980
Just wait.

363
00:30:18,120 --> 00:30:20,520
You think... I can do it?

364
00:30:20,960 --> 00:30:23,440
Well, just do it first.
You might like it.

365
00:30:25,480 --> 00:30:28,640
Honestly, I still
don't know what I'm into.

366
00:30:29,380 --> 00:30:32,400
I'm not sure if I like
the univ program I got into.

367
00:30:33,200 --> 00:30:34,410
My scores got me in.

368
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:37,800
Not everyone figures out
what they like right away.

369
00:30:38,720 --> 00:30:42,690
But right now, there's one thing
I'm sure...

370
00:30:43,670 --> 00:30:44,720
that I like.

371
00:30:48,890 --> 00:30:50,010
I like you.

372
00:31:01,730 --> 00:31:02,730
Hmm.

373
00:31:04,210 --> 00:31:05,440
Are you still mad at me?

374
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:10,800
From the way I've been,
you think I'm still mad?

375
00:31:11,150 --> 00:31:12,150
For real?

376
00:31:12,720 --> 00:31:13,960
You're not mad anymore?

377
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:16,040
Yeah.

378
00:31:18,110 --> 00:31:18,590
Yes!

379
00:31:18,640 --> 00:31:21,390
Best thing that's happened to me
in days.

380
00:31:21,890 --> 00:31:23,740
- Woo...
- Get down here.

381
00:31:28,160 --> 00:31:30,000
I'm nice to you a bit,
and your ego takes off?

382
00:31:30,040 --> 00:31:31,600
Just a little. Come here.

383
00:31:33,440 --> 00:31:34,680
- Hey, that's mine.
- Hmm.

384
00:31:35,570 --> 00:31:36,640
Wow, that's good.

385
00:31:43,190 --> 00:31:45,360
- We're here.
- Go play ball.

386
00:31:48,330 --> 00:31:49,450
Hurry up.

387
00:31:49,700 --> 00:31:50,799
Home sweet home.

388
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:55,280
Alright, engine's off,
everyone out.

389
00:31:55,540 --> 00:31:58,310
- Yay...
- Go on, go on.

390
00:31:58,330 --> 00:32:00,600
- Okay, kids. Slowly.
- Thank you.

391
00:32:00,640 --> 00:32:01,799
- Go on.
- Thank you.

392
00:32:01,800 --> 00:32:04,650
Oh, don't jump. Careful, careful.

393
00:32:04,680 --> 00:32:06,129
- Thank you.
- Okay, good.

394
00:32:06,130 --> 00:32:07,560
Thank you, Uncle Sorn.

395
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:09,800
Hey, watch it.
Walk carefully, this one.

396
00:32:09,820 --> 00:32:11,279
Haha.

397
00:32:11,280 --> 00:32:12,600
- Hello.
- Come on.

398
00:32:12,740 --> 00:32:14,640
Snow. Hey, Snow.

399
00:32:16,470 --> 00:32:18,670
Uncle Sun's coming
for dinner tonight, okay?

400
00:32:19,750 --> 00:32:20,750
Mm-hmm.

401
00:32:29,530 --> 00:32:31,120
What's gotten into her?

402
00:32:32,640 --> 00:32:34,360
Aren't you two still fighting?

403
00:32:35,460 --> 00:32:38,040
Oh, right. I forgot.

404
00:32:38,400 --> 00:32:40,320
You haven't talked to her in days.

405
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:42,920
She's been wanting to talk to you,
you know?

406
00:32:46,580 --> 00:32:47,600
Thanks.

407
00:32:48,660 --> 00:32:49,760
- Lets' go.
- Yeah.

408
00:32:58,030 --> 00:32:59,120
Grandpa.

409
00:33:02,200 --> 00:33:03,400
Hello.

410
00:33:06,520 --> 00:33:07,520
Oof.

411
00:33:14,340 --> 00:33:16,160
Oh, thank you so much. Thank you.

412
00:33:17,200 --> 00:33:18,520
Go do whatever you need to do.

413
00:33:18,920 --> 00:33:19,920
Thank you.

414
00:33:32,040 --> 00:33:34,360
Hey, aren't you going after her?

415
00:33:37,720 --> 00:33:40,920
Don't like me nagging you?
Then don't go nagging Snow.

416
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:43,280
Understand?

417
00:34:19,910 --> 00:34:22,500
- Nothing to do?
- Mm-hmm.

418
00:34:24,490 --> 00:34:25,800
I thought everybody was busy.

419
00:34:26,360 --> 00:34:29,880
Well, just a few things
to take care of.

420
00:34:31,240 --> 00:34:32,520
You can get back to it.

421
00:34:36,550 --> 00:34:40,280
About the other day, I'm sorry
for being so harsh with you.

422
00:34:41,310 --> 00:34:43,480
I just want you to study hard.

423
00:34:44,500 --> 00:34:45,720
So you don't end up like me.

424
00:34:52,200 --> 00:34:53,600
You're not that bad, Dad.

425
00:34:54,750 --> 00:34:56,070
Just a little clueless sometimes.

426
00:34:56,480 --> 00:34:57,480
Oh yeah?

427
00:34:58,840 --> 00:35:02,760
I'm not mad anymore.
I said some bad things too.

428
00:35:19,400 --> 00:35:20,400
Hmm.

429
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:29,040
Are we good, Dad?

430
00:35:31,360 --> 00:35:32,360
Mm-hmm.

431
00:35:33,720 --> 00:35:34,720
We're good.

432
00:35:36,200 --> 00:35:38,340
And... I'll keep this

433
00:35:38,670 --> 00:35:43,640
as a reminder
not to do that to you again.

434
00:35:46,120 --> 00:35:47,720
- But one more thing.
- Hmm?

435
00:35:47,900 --> 00:35:50,919
I know I need to study harder.

436
00:35:50,920 --> 00:35:54,040
But you could just tell me nicely.
No need for the whole drama.

437
00:35:56,020 --> 00:36:00,000
Okay, your dad is dramatic.

438
00:36:01,720 --> 00:36:02,720
Big time.

439
00:36:03,430 --> 00:36:06,710
Now I'll read a novel.
Haven't touched it in a while.

440
00:36:07,160 --> 00:36:08,160
Heh.

441
00:36:32,680 --> 00:36:35,120
Oh, Sun, you're here.

442
00:36:37,830 --> 00:36:38,830
Mart. Mart.

443
00:36:39,200 --> 00:36:40,920
Mart, Sun's here.

444
00:36:42,280 --> 00:36:43,400
Hello, Father.

445
00:36:44,240 --> 00:36:45,240
Hello.

446
00:36:47,160 --> 00:36:49,520
I told you not to bring too much.

447
00:36:49,810 --> 00:36:51,000
Just a little, Phi Mart.

448
00:36:51,890 --> 00:36:52,890
Let me take that.

449
00:36:53,080 --> 00:36:55,160
Come, the table's all set. Come in.

450
00:37:05,720 --> 00:37:07,080
Wow.

451
00:37:10,200 --> 00:37:12,279
I wish Uncle Sun came for dinner
every night.

452
00:37:12,280 --> 00:37:13,840
I'd get to eat a lot.

453
00:37:14,320 --> 00:37:16,300
- Heh...
- Snow.

454
00:37:18,760 --> 00:37:19,760
Oof.

455
00:37:20,880 --> 00:37:21,880
Hot.

456
00:37:21,930 --> 00:37:24,160
Dad, blow on it first.

457
00:37:24,280 --> 00:37:25,440
I like it hot.

458
00:37:26,890 --> 00:37:28,240
Mmm...

459
00:37:40,010 --> 00:37:41,010
Grandpa?

460
00:37:50,200 --> 00:37:51,440
Better now?

461
00:37:54,780 --> 00:37:58,020
Oh-ho...

462
00:37:58,760 --> 00:38:00,640
You've been dethroned, Dad.

463
00:38:00,790 --> 00:38:02,879
Look.
Uncle Sun is his favorite now.

464
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:05,560
Oh, he always has been.

465
00:38:05,580 --> 00:38:07,120
Heh...

466
00:38:15,520 --> 00:38:16,560
Eat up.

467
00:38:16,860 --> 00:38:19,100
- Aw...
- Uh-hmm...

468
00:38:19,120 --> 00:38:20,120
Yes, Dad.

469
00:38:20,220 --> 00:38:22,590
Dad, serve me some too.

470
00:38:22,630 --> 00:38:24,040
Here you go.

471
00:38:44,880 --> 00:38:47,010
- Feeling better now?
- Mm-hmm.

472
00:38:47,320 --> 00:38:49,240
Uncle Sun helped
with the first payment.

473
00:38:50,320 --> 00:38:51,680
You can take it easy now.

474
00:38:52,330 --> 00:38:55,120
And I just picked up a tutoring gig.

475
00:38:55,400 --> 00:38:56,640
I'll help chip in too.

476
00:38:58,670 --> 00:39:01,790
Save, I want to get back to writing.

477
00:39:02,390 --> 00:39:06,000
Grandpa, if you're doing that
just for the money,

478
00:39:07,480 --> 00:39:08,840
I think you should take a break.

479
00:39:10,420 --> 00:39:13,620
Everyone is finding
other ways to earn.

480
00:39:14,200 --> 00:39:15,880
I want to earn too.

481
00:39:16,790 --> 00:39:18,680
And I still think about...

482
00:39:20,970 --> 00:39:24,920
Somporn and Anan's unfinished story.

483
00:39:27,000 --> 00:39:30,000
A writer can't abandon
their characters

484
00:39:30,920 --> 00:39:34,000
or their readers.

485
00:39:35,390 --> 00:39:36,560
That's so cool, Grandpa.

486
00:39:37,190 --> 00:39:40,440
But...
my eyes aren't the same anymore.

487
00:39:41,280 --> 00:39:43,920
I'll need your help with that.

488
00:39:44,800 --> 00:39:47,640
Of course. Just say the word.

489
00:39:51,070 --> 00:39:52,280
Try to speak now.

490
00:39:57,610 --> 00:39:59,760
Chapter twelve.

491
00:40:01,960 --> 00:40:03,360
Wow, nice.

492
00:40:05,400 --> 00:40:07,840
- Hey, hey. Delete it, delete.
- Wait.

493
00:40:08,320 --> 00:40:09,760
Only speak what you want to write.

494
00:40:10,920 --> 00:40:11,920
Hmm? Start over.

495
00:40:14,320 --> 00:40:15,320
Go ahead.

496
00:40:17,720 --> 00:40:18,840
Somporn...

497
00:40:20,230 --> 00:40:24,580
and Anan looked up
at the wide-open sky.

498
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:27,240
Typo again.

499
00:40:28,770 --> 00:40:31,670
- Keep going. I'll fix it later.
- Yeah, yeah.

500
00:40:31,690 --> 00:40:38,079
Somporn and Anan looked up
at the wide-open sky.

501
00:40:38,080 --> 00:40:41,760
The deep grey of the storm clouds.
Hey...

502
00:40:42,120 --> 00:40:44,440
It makes a bunch of mistakes.

503
00:40:46,280 --> 00:40:48,039
Here, I'll type it.

504
00:40:48,040 --> 00:40:49,040
Hmph.

505
00:40:53,760 --> 00:40:54,760
Go ahead, Grandpa.

506
00:40:56,750 --> 00:40:59,800
Somporn and Anan looked up
at the wide-open sky.

507
00:41:00,520 --> 00:41:02,520
The deep grey of the storm clouds

508
00:41:03,330 --> 00:41:05,520
crept in, little by little.

509
00:41:06,200 --> 00:41:07,280
Lightning

510
00:41:08,540 --> 00:41:11,560
cracked like a gunshot.

511
00:41:15,290 --> 00:41:16,610
Rain

512
00:41:18,130 --> 00:41:20,920
came pouring down

513
00:41:21,800 --> 00:41:25,200
and swallowed the road ahead.

514
00:41:28,640 --> 00:41:30,040
No matter what obstacles

515
00:41:32,020 --> 00:41:34,120
the two of them were facing,

516
00:41:36,040 --> 00:41:37,200
however steep the climb,

517
00:41:37,430 --> 00:41:42,080
as long as they walked hand in hand,

518
00:41:43,960 --> 00:41:48,600
nothing could stand in their way.

519
00:41:59,630 --> 00:42:01,259
"Publish now."

520
00:42:01,260 --> 00:42:02,740
"Success."

521
00:42:06,200 --> 00:42:08,000
"Missed this so much..."

522
00:42:08,190 --> 00:42:10,000
"Thought you'd dropped us for good."

523
00:42:10,200 --> 00:42:14,420
"Thanks for coming back.
This really means a lot..."

524
00:42:46,680 --> 00:42:48,960
Hey, Phi Sorn, easy.

525
00:42:49,460 --> 00:42:51,319
It's dough, not cement.

526
00:42:51,320 --> 00:42:52,879
Oh, I always do it like this.

527
00:42:52,880 --> 00:42:54,200
That's way too hard.

528
00:42:54,280 --> 00:42:55,440
- Like this?
- Hey.

529
00:42:55,470 --> 00:42:58,680
Heh.

530
00:43:07,280 --> 00:43:08,580
- Hey.
- Nice, right?

531
00:43:08,610 --> 00:43:11,720
- Look at you, pretty good.
- It's called craft.

532
00:43:14,380 --> 00:43:17,000
Not bad, not bad. First timer too.

533
00:43:18,250 --> 00:43:19,930
I didn't press too hard, right?

534
00:43:20,520 --> 00:43:22,400
- Like this?
- Yeah, that works.

535
00:43:23,890 --> 00:43:25,800
What's that? Taking a photo?

536
00:43:25,820 --> 00:43:26,380
Heh.

537
00:43:26,400 --> 00:43:28,959
Ho... if you want it, just say so.

538
00:43:28,960 --> 00:43:30,080
Here. Hmph.

539
00:43:31,560 --> 00:43:35,640
Hmm... alright, smile.

540
00:43:36,170 --> 00:43:40,080
Click. Aw... closer, closer.

541
00:43:41,180 --> 00:43:42,840
Yeah.

542
00:44:29,880 --> 00:44:31,880
Hello, where are you?

543
00:44:32,160 --> 00:44:34,200
I'm here. Are you done tutoring?

544
00:44:34,480 --> 00:44:35,720
Yeah, I'll walk over to you.

545
00:44:39,590 --> 00:44:40,590
Where are you?

546
00:44:42,520 --> 00:44:43,560
Turn around.

547
00:44:52,960 --> 00:44:56,480
Hey, how'd you get that?
I threw it away.

548
00:44:58,120 --> 00:45:00,040
Well, you put me through a lot.

549
00:45:39,120 --> 00:45:40,120
Tch.

550
00:45:49,750 --> 00:45:51,160
So you... kept it?

551
00:45:51,720 --> 00:45:53,680
Are you crazy?
You could've gotten hit.

552
00:45:54,030 --> 00:45:56,200
You're the crazy one.
Why'd you throw it?

553
00:45:56,570 --> 00:45:58,120
Because you didn't want it.

554
00:45:58,970 --> 00:46:00,520
I'm wearing it, aren't I?

555
00:46:07,470 --> 00:46:08,680
Hey, what?

556
00:46:09,760 --> 00:46:11,080
Now that we've made up.

557
00:46:13,180 --> 00:46:16,280
What are we now?

558
00:46:18,680 --> 00:46:19,760
We're friends.

559
00:46:21,120 --> 00:46:22,400
Nothing more?

560
00:46:23,040 --> 00:46:24,160
How much more do you want?

561
00:46:25,320 --> 00:46:26,400
Come on.

562
00:46:27,260 --> 00:46:30,140
You're the one who asked me.
Remember?

563
00:46:30,760 --> 00:46:32,800
I don't know. I forgot.

564
00:46:33,960 --> 00:46:34,960
Come on.

565
00:46:36,400 --> 00:46:38,480
I don't want to hide anymore.

566
00:46:39,760 --> 00:46:40,840
You get me, right?

567
00:46:59,200 --> 00:47:00,200
Guy.

568
00:47:07,480 --> 00:47:09,519
- Here you go.
- Wow.

569
00:47:09,520 --> 00:47:10,380
Here you go.

570
00:47:10,400 --> 00:47:12,320
- Wow.
- Wow...

571
00:47:13,940 --> 00:47:15,640
And here.

572
00:47:15,790 --> 00:47:18,800
Kids, say thank you to Uncle Sun.

573
00:47:19,280 --> 00:47:22,440
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

574
00:47:22,710 --> 00:47:25,000
Well, I'll come by more often, okay?

575
00:47:25,320 --> 00:47:27,080
- Yes.
- Yes.

576
00:47:27,240 --> 00:47:29,240
Alright everyone, let's eat.

577
00:48:04,470 --> 00:48:05,560
- Dad.
- Hmm.

578
00:48:07,950 --> 00:48:08,950
Hurry, Dad.

579
00:48:11,320 --> 00:48:13,080
Hold this. I'll do it.

580
00:48:14,660 --> 00:48:16,760
- Ow, come here. Look.
- Mm-hmm.

581
00:48:21,520 --> 00:48:22,670
Hmph.

582
00:48:22,700 --> 00:48:23,700
This isn't going well.

583
00:48:24,080 --> 00:48:27,620
- Be careful. Watch the frosting.
- Hold on.

584
00:48:28,200 --> 00:48:29,280
Got it, got it.

585
00:48:30,910 --> 00:48:31,840
Hit it. Hit it.

586
00:48:31,860 --> 00:48:32,860
Hit it.

587
00:48:33,150 --> 00:48:33,980
Hit it.

588
00:48:34,000 --> 00:48:35,079
Go, go.

589
00:48:35,080 --> 00:48:37,280
Careful, don't fall.

590
00:48:39,880 --> 00:48:40,920
Got it.

591
00:48:43,270 --> 00:48:44,320
Snow.

592
00:48:46,830 --> 00:48:52,720
Happy Birthday to Snow.

593
00:48:53,000 --> 00:48:56,160
- Happy Birthday, Snow.
- Happy Birthday, Snow.

594
00:49:01,370 --> 00:49:02,960
Make a wish, Snow.

595
00:49:18,070 --> 00:49:19,720
Oy, that's too many wishes.

596
00:49:24,970 --> 00:49:27,520
- Yay...
- Yay...

597
00:49:31,320 --> 00:49:36,440
I just wish for
Saeng Karun to stay forever.

598
00:49:37,040 --> 00:49:39,560
I want to be with everyone
like this for a long, long time.

599
00:49:44,440 --> 00:49:45,590
That's so sweet.

600
00:49:49,140 --> 00:49:52,240
Uncle Sun, we put together
a show for you as a thank you.

601
00:49:54,270 --> 00:49:55,270
Quick, everyone, go.

602
00:49:55,300 --> 00:49:56,400
Hurry, everyone.

603
00:49:58,820 --> 00:49:59,820
There's a show.

604
00:50:00,150 --> 00:50:01,510
Did anyone know about this?

605
00:50:04,360 --> 00:50:06,120
- Woo...
- Woo...

606
00:50:12,340 --> 00:50:13,890
Oh, you look beautiful, sweetheart.

607
00:50:18,340 --> 00:50:19,340
Hey, here we go.

608
00:50:24,690 --> 00:50:26,840
Snow. Snow.

609
00:50:44,160 --> 00:50:45,320
Look at that outfit.

610
00:50:45,660 --> 00:50:47,320
Wow.

611
00:50:47,340 --> 00:50:49,210
- Wow...
- Wow...

612
00:51:56,030 --> 00:51:57,030
Woo.

613
00:52:15,870 --> 00:52:20,040
- Woo...
- Woo...

614
00:52:59,070 --> 00:53:03,040
Save, I think... I'm ready.

615
00:53:03,450 --> 00:53:04,450
Ready for what?

616
00:53:07,820 --> 00:53:10,540
"Between Us in the Deep Forest."

617
00:53:10,560 --> 00:53:12,960
They want us to sign
with the studio.

618
00:53:12,990 --> 00:53:15,759
Going off to be an actor,
and you didn't think to ask me?

619
00:53:15,760 --> 00:53:17,119
Can't open the file, Grandpa.

620
00:53:17,120 --> 00:53:18,319
How's it going, sir?

621
00:53:18,320 --> 00:53:20,639
We've been expecting your file
as discussed.

622
00:53:20,640 --> 00:53:23,520
Can I have a little more time
to fix it up?

623
00:53:24,040 --> 00:53:25,040
Guy.

624
00:53:27,120 --> 00:53:28,280
Be my boyfriend.

625
00:53:30,710 --> 00:53:36,519
The world keeps
turning every day.

626
00:53:36,520 --> 00:53:41,759
And we keep
turning in its play.

627
00:53:41,760 --> 00:53:45,119
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

628
00:53:45,120 --> 00:53:47,799
We just might see
the world within.

629
00:53:47,800 --> 00:53:51,919
Let's walk together,
day by day.

630
00:53:51,920 --> 00:53:56,880
Come take the step,
what do you say?

631
00:54:03,420 --> 00:54:07,060
Let us be real,
not dreaming away,

632
00:54:07,080 --> 00:54:10,949
We'll walk in the light
of a new day.

633
00:54:10,950 --> 00:54:16,039
No one can tell
what tomorrow may say.

634
00:54:16,040 --> 00:54:18,399
Wherever the gentle wind blows,

635
00:54:18,400 --> 00:54:21,279
let our hearts flow,
soft and slow.

636
00:54:21,280 --> 00:54:26,080
And land where
our hearts both grow.

637
00:54:26,440 --> 00:54:32,359
The world keeps
turning every day.

638
00:54:32,360 --> 00:54:37,639
And we keep
turning in its play.

639
00:54:37,640 --> 00:54:40,919
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

640
